explanation: The code initialized the set of digits with range(1, 10), which omitted 0. If the input string was missing '0', the program would produce an empty set and print nothing. I fixed that line to use range(10) so the set contains 0â€“9. (This mirrors the kind of range-start change seen in Diff 4 where the range was adjusted to include 0.)
fixed_code:
S = input()
num = set([i for i in range(10)])

for s in S:
    num.discard(int(s))

print(*num)
